President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New Hampshire due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from March 2 to March 8, 2018. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement State and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, particularly in Rockingham County. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. James N. Russo has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.